node.text:
We've driven the updated Kia Stinger GT S! 🎉

It has a new active exhaust, although it's V6 still sounds pretty underwhelming.
We can forgive it for that, as the Stinger is still a riot to drive, with amusingly low traction limits even in the dry.

It feels a lot quicker than the factory figures suggest, and it's now nicer inside, with improved materials and a better infotainment system.

Sadly, it might not be around for much longer - it's thought Kia might pull the plug as early as 2022.

We'll miss it when it's gone.

node.text:
We tried out the Aston Martin F1 Edition recently!

It's a road-going version of the new F1 safety car, featuring the same rear wing and front splitter combo plus 21-inch wheels. You don't get the flashing lights, though - sorry.

We're not completely sold on the visual tweaks, but the fettled chassis is definitely a winner - this is the best-driving Vantage yet.

The 4.0-litre AMG-sourced V8 now produces 528bhp, and despite the use of particulate filters, it still sounds great.

It is expensive, though, with a starting price of £142,000 in the UK - you could get a Porsche 911 GTS for that and be left with a whole heap of change.

What do you think of the F1 Edition? 🤔
